article.headline: Texas-San Antonio 76, Cameron 48
article.story: SAN ANTONIO -- Jordan Sims scored 14 points, all in the second half, and UTSA rolled to a 76-48 victory over Cameron on Sunday. The Roadrunners (4-3) trailed 29-28 at halftime, but scored the first 23 points of the second half to put the game out of reach. Kannon Burrage added 13 points for UTSA. Jeromie Hill had 11 points and Stephen Franklin scored 10 -- eight during the 23-0 second-half run. Vinicius Telo led the Aggies with 13 points and seven rebounds. Cameron, which plays in Division II, led by as many as nine points during the first half. UTSA forced 24 turnovers that led to 26 points for the Roadrunners.
